# Cloudflare Pages / Netlify _redirects
# Cloudflare Pages reads this from the dist/ output directory.
# Vite copies everything in public/ to dist/ so this file is included automatically.

# ── Trailing-slash redirects for service area pages ────────────────────────
# Non-forced: static files always take precedence.
# When a prerendered dist/path/index.html exists, the platform serves it
# directly and these rules never fire. They only fire for the no-trailing-slash
# variant of each URL (e.g. /house-clearance-reading), which has no static file
# (only the /house-clearance-reading/ directory has index.html).
# One clean 301 → trailing-slash URL → prerendered file served directly.
/waste-removal-*               /waste-removal-:splat/               301
/house-clearance-*             /house-clearance-:splat/             301
/end-of-tenancy-clearance-*    /end-of-tenancy-clearance-:splat/    301
/garden-waste-removal-*        /garden-waste-removal-:splat/        301
/commercial-waste-removal-*    /commercial-waste-removal-:splat/    301
/construction-waste-removal-*  /construction-waste-removal-:splat/  301
/garage-shed-clearance-*       /garage-shed-clearance-:splat/       301

# SPA fallback — serve index.html for any path that doesn't match a static file.
# Prerendered HTML files (dist/waste-removal-reading/index.html etc.) are
# served directly as static files before this rule is ever reached.
/*    /index.html    200
